# Report on the Frequency of Defensive Gun Use in the United States

## Introduction

The use of firearms for self-defense, commonly referred to as Defensive Gun Use (DGU), is a highly debated and contentious issue in the United States. Estimates of how often guns are used in self-defense vary widely, ranging from tens of thousands to several million incidents annually. This report provides a comprehensive and detailed analysis of the frequency of defensive gun use, drawing from a variety of sources including academic studies, government surveys, and recent research. The goal is to present an objective, data-driven perspective on how often people use guns for self-defense, highlighting the methodological challenges and discrepancies in existing research.

---

## Overview of Defensive Gun Use Estimates

### Wide Range of Estimates

Estimates of the annual number of defensive gun uses in the U.S. vary dramatically depending on the source and methodology:

| Source/Study                      | Estimated Annual DGUs          | Methodology/Notes                                                                                     |
|----------------------------------|-------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Kleck & Gertz (1995)              | 2.2 to 2.5 million            | National random-digit-dial telephone survey; criticized for potential overestimation                 |
| National Crime Victimization Survey (NCVS) | ~100,000 to 235,000            | Victim interviews; considered more conservative and reliable by some experts                         |
| Cook & Ludwig (1997)              | 1.46 to 4.7 million           | Analysis of NSPOF survey; questioned credibility of higher estimates                                |
| Harvard Injury Control Research Center (Hemenway, 2016) | ~0.9% of crimes involve DGU (~100,000) | Analysis of NCVS data from 2007-2011; emphasizes rarity of DGU                                      |
| 2021 National Firearms Survey     | 1.67 million (potentially up to 2.8 million) | Large internet survey of gun owners; extrapolated to national population                            |
| Violence Policy Center (2013)     | ~67,740                       | FBI data analysis; lower estimate based on verified incidents                                      |
| Gun Violence Archive (2016-2017) | ~2,000 incidents              | Media and law enforcement reports; undercounts non-reported DGUs                                   |

*Table 1: Summary of Defensive Gun Use Estimates from Various Sources*

