## Detailed Findings from Key Studies and Surveys

### Kleck and Gertz (1995)

- Estimated 2.2 to 2.5 million DGUs annually based on a telephone survey of 5,000 people.

- Found that 31.1% of gun owners reported at least one DGU in their lifetime.

- Criticized for implausible numbers of assailants shot compared to hospital and police records.

- Kleck argues many DGUs go unreported to police or hospitals due to fear of legal complications ([Kleck & Gertz, 1995](https://doi.org/10.2307/1144004)).

### National Crime Victimization Survey (NCVS)

- Estimates around 100,000 to 235,000 DGUs per year.

- Uses victim reports of crimes; only asks about DGU if the respondent reports being a crime victim.

- Likely undercounts DGUs because many defensive incidents do not involve recognized crimes or are not reported ([Bureau of Justice Statistics, 2013](https://bjs.ojp.gov/content/pub/pdf/fv9311.pdf)).

### Harvard Injury Control Research Center (Hemenway)

- Analysis of NCVS data from 2007-2011 found DGU in 0.9% of crimes.

- Argues risks of gun ownership outweigh benefits due to rarity of DGU and potential for misuse.

- Notes that running away or calling police often leads to better outcomes than using a gun defensively ([Hemenway & Solnick, 2015](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ypmed.2015.03.029)).

### 2021 National Firearms Survey

- Surveyed 54,000 Americans, including 16,000 gun owners.

- Estimated 1.67 million DGUs annually, possibly up to 2.8 million.

- Found that in 81.9% of DGUs, no shots were fired; showing or verbally indicating a gun was often sufficient.

- Majority of DGUs occurred on the gun owner’s property (79.1%).

- Multiple assailants were involved in over half of the incidents ([English et al., 2021](https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3887145)).

### Gun Violence Archive and Media Reports

- Reported fewer than 2,100 verified defensive gun use incidents annually (2016-2017).

- Likely underestimates due to reliance on reported and verified incidents only ([Gun Violence Archive, 2018](https://www.gunviolencearchive.org)).

